svg.script: // Define timeline without setting it var svgTimeLine // Start Animation function startAnimation(){ // set timeLine svgTimeLine = new TimelineMax // Define container ID var svgContainerID = document.getElementById('svgContainer'); svgTimeLine.set([svgContainerID],{autoAlpha:1}) svgTimeLine.set("#caption01,#bubble01,#caption02,#bubble02",{x:50}) svgTimeLine.set("#Julie,#Morris,#hand",{scale:1.04, transformOrigin:"center center"}) svgTimeLine.to("#Julie,#Morris,#hand",3,{scale:1, transformOrigin:"center center"}) svgTimeLine.to("#caption01,#bubble01",0.5,{x:0, autoAlpha:1},0.1) svgTimeLine.to("#caption02,#bubble02",0.5,{x:0, autoAlpha:1},0.3) svgTimeLine.to("#title",0.5,{autoAlpha:1},0.5) // Get duration for each path // Animate the stroke-dashoffset to 0 to give the appearance of being written. // We are using this technique for Browser compatibility and to avoid using the gsap DrawSVG plugin. } window.addEventListener('load',function(){ startAnimation() },false);
